S|# 11 · YouTube Analytics (Long-form)|> Performance view for the long-form channel — how published videos are doing, feeding back into ideas and titling.
S|Purpose|Track long-form video performance (views, retention, CTR, subscriber impact) so the cnt engine learns what works and feeds those learnings back into the cnt pl (ideas) and YouTube Studio (titles/thumbnails).
S|What it covers (inferred)|- Per-video and channel-level metrics: views, watch time/retention, click-through rate on thumbnails/titles, subscribers gained. // - Trends over time and comparisons between videos (which title/thumbnail patterns win) — consistent with Henry's data-informed title coaching in YouTube Studio. // - Insights that loop back into **cnt pl** ideas and **Trend Radar** cnt recommendations.
S|Relationship to other screens|- Downstream of **YouTube Studio** (`10`) and **cnt pl** (`08`). // - Complements **soc anl** (`16`), which covers posts across soc platforms rather than long-form YouTube. // > **Confidence:** Listed in the sidebar (LONG-FORM section) and an "anl" entry point appears in YouTube Studio, but a dedicated anl screen was not captured. Contents above are *inferred* from its name and role.